        myPreferredSize

      • myPreferredSize

        public final java.awt.Dimension myPreferredSize
        overridden preferred size. Never null. Term "overridden" means that GridLayoutManager gets preferred size from the constrains first. Moreover if one of the returned dimensions (x or y) is negative then the corresponding dimension is also calculated by the component. It means that it's possible to override any particular dimension without subclassing of the component. Stantard Swing doesn't have such capability.
